The raw runs confirmed all mandated ordinary validation paths and the combined ledger’s hand-computed totals. They also exposed two contract edge failures: unchecked large integer amounts can serialize financial fields as `null`, and duplicate conflict classification is bypassed when the later duplicate also fails field validation. I’m doing the final syntax and exact-schema checks before issuing the findings-only verdict.
